Discover 10 different types of locks in use.

I observed different types of locks used in daily life to understand physical security methods.
Padlock – Used on gates and storage units
Deadbolt Lock – Used on home doors for extra security
Knob Lock – Commonly used on room doors
Lever Handle Lock – Found in offices and commercial buildings
Smart Lock – Digital lock controlled via phone or code
Biometric Lock – Uses fingerprint for access
Combination Lock – Requires a number code
Cam Lock – Used in cabinets and drawers
Mortise Lock – Installed inside doors for stronger protection
Chain Lock – Used as an additional door security layer


These locks show how different security levels are used depending on the situation and risk.
